org.junit.jupiter.params.provider

Annotation Type ValueSource


  • @Target(value={ANNOTATION_TYPE,METHOD})
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Documented
 @API(status=EXPERIMENTAL,
     since="5.0")
 @ArgumentsSource(value=org.junit.jupiter.params.provider.ValueArgumentsProvider.class)
public @interface ValueSource
    @ValueSource is an ArgumentsSource which provides access to an array of literal values of primitive types.

    Supported primitive types include strings(), ints(), longs(), and doubles(). You must not specify more than one annotation attribute.

    The supplied literal values will be provided as arguments to the annotated @ParameterizedTest method.

    Since:
    5.0
    See Also:
    ArgumentsSource, ParameterizedTest
